romwellian conquest in the 1650s helped forge a new Irish Catholic national identity. Following a successful hardback edition, Ó Siochrú and OIhlmeyer's popular title is now available in paperback. The original and wide-ranging themes chosen by leading international scholars for this volume will ensure that this edited collection becomes required reading for all those interested in the history of early modern Europe. It will also appeal to those engaged in early colonial studies in the Atlantic world and beyond, as the volume adopts a genuinely comparative approach throughout, examining developments in a broad global context.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Modern / 17th Century.2bisacsh  a1641 rebellion.  aBarcelona publications.  aBernandino Beccari.  aCromwellian conquest.  aDutch Revolt.  aFrench wars of religion.  aIrish Black Legend.  aIrish Catholic national identity.  aIrish exiles.  aIrish wars.  aProtestant/ British identity.  aSpanish Black Legend.  aSpanish Monarchy.  aThirty Years' War.  aatrocity stories.1 aCanny, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Aidan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreengrass, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiernan, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuijpers, Erika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKupperman, Karen Ordahl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorgan, Hiram, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOhlmeyer, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOhlmey